text.tspan: Unstopped, the flow from Jesus’ side
Consecration — Constrained by the Lord’s Love
Agape love then bids me be
No more for my own gain;
For He who loved and rescued me
Has won my life through pain.
Can one who’s loved not give his all?
A life that daily dies, then lives,
To know the riches of His grace,
Emotion, mind, and will I place
I sense His will and turn aside
I walk and yield each choice;
In daily steps, both small and great,
Each time His will defeats my own,
Each vict’ry o’er my self-bound soul
